		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Jan 26th 5:18 AM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=98045047624832&num=3&page=&post=1&replyto=98048614316750"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=98048614316750></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=23265"><span id=>bede</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>1 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=bede&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>This skill increases refreshingly fast.&nbsp;&nbsp;To get my skill up during otherwise wasted time, while selling in EC, I just wandered around looking for Orc Pawns and Skellies with weapons, walked up to them and hit disarm repeatedly.  You can disarm an NPC without killing it, but disarm agroes it, so you really have to kill it anyway.  It isn't like a pickpocket skill.  I find that it works slightly less than once per fight with my skill in the low 90s.  I just add it to my circle of hot keys in open areas...special attack....disarm.....instill doubt, minus ID in dungeons.  If it works, gravy, and the weapon drops at your feet.  I don't have enough experience with it to say how much damage is mitigated, but it isn't like it costs anything to use.  The annoying thing for me is that it seems to work at the end of the fight a lot, after the bad guy has already gotten plenty of use out of his weapon.  It's not on par with FD, but it's easy and gives you one more thing to do during melee.    </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
